    • Method Detail

      • itemsChanged

        void itemsChanged(java.util.List events)
        Notifies of the given events affecting shared items.

        The events are in the order in which they occurred, with the earliest ones at the beginning of the list. The list of events may contain more than one entry for the same shared item.

        Implement this method to react of the given events. The implementation must not do significant work; it must assume it is running in a thread that must be kept responsive, and behave accordingly.

        Parameters:
        events - the list of events (element type: ISharedItemChangeEvent); list must not be null; elements must not be null
